{"text": "I’ve always wanted to understand how experienced developers decide what to build first and how they break big ideas into manageable steps.

In Plan mode, I asked how to turn a simple app idea into a structured development plan. From the conversation, I learned that building software is less about coding everything at once and more about defining a clear user flow, identifying the core problem, and prioritizing features based on impact. I also learned the importance of starting with a minimal, valuable version (MVP), testing it early, and improving it through iteration.

The biggest insight for me was that good software is usually the result of thoughtful planning and gradual refinement — not a single perfect build.", "title": "Your turn: Try Plan mode", "description": "What have you always wanted to know about building software? Go to Lovable, switch to Plan mode, and ask your question.", "subDescription": "What did you learn about building software from your conversation in Plan mode?"}

{"text": "I prompted a small improvement: add validation to prevent empty submissions, clear the input fields after adding a suggestion, and include a delete button for each entry. After applying it, the change was mostly close to what I had in mind—the flow felt smoother and it was harder to accidentally add bad data.

However, it also surfaced something I’d describe more precisely next time. For example, I’d specify exactly what the validation message should say and confirm whether suggestions should persist after a page refresh (local storage or database). Overall, I noticed that a small, focused prompt led to a very specific, easy-to-test change without breaking the rest of the app.", "title": "Your turn: Improve your app", "description": "Prompt an improvement to your app in Lovable. Then take a moment to reflect on what happened.

Was the change close to what you had in mind, or did it surface something you’d describe differently next time?", "subDescription": "Notice how a small, focused prompt led to a specific change."}

{"text": "test", "title": "Your turn: Try planning mode", "description": "Enable planning mode and ask Lovable to add a feature to your app.

Watch how it breaks down the problem before building. Decide whether you like the plan or want to adjust it.

What feature did you ask for? What did the plan look like?", "subDescription": "Planning mode is useful for complex features where you want to review the approach before building."}
